column2: " This data was previously collected and presented for mainstream households only. We are no longer able to split the data on deregistrations by household type.

° A number of households had exemptions in place which allowed them to accommodate more children than they were approved for. As a result a slightly larger number of places were reported as filled, vacant or unavailable than the number of approved places.
? A small number of IFAs submitted data on brothers and sisters when they should not have done so. We have therefore discounted this data from these tables

~ In 2014-15 and 2015-16, data was collected on family and friends households and on 'connected person' households separately. From 2016-17 onwards, data on both household types was collected together as family and friends. Households approved in year have been classified as family and friends households if their primary placement offer is reported as family and friends.
? Deregistered shared care households have been excluded where the household type at deregistration has been supplied.

* Data on TSD standards has previously been presented by household type. In 2018-19, this data is presented for all carers, by status of their TSD standards. This reflects the way in which the data is collected.
^ One agency reported an unusually high number of IRM referrals in 2018 to 2019. This data has been excluded from the national figure.
** Recruitment outcomes data relates to those applications received in-year only.
